cs.LO, cs.DM, cs.PL, cs.GT, cs.CC

The paper deals with a combinatorial approach to the program of Geometry of Interaction, which is a topic in mathematical logic. The paper introduces a generalization of graphs named graphings, which is a geometric realization of a graph. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with combinatorial structures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also deals with models of linear logic, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
